adjectives.description: unfree (comparative more unfree or unfreer or unfree-er, superlative most unfree or unfreest or unfree-est)

entries.meaning: Not free; lacking freedom, especially (historical) of a tenant who was bound to a manor.
examples: Economically free countries enjoy decentralized power, whereas the power in economically unfree countries is centralized.

entries.meaning: (historical) A person lacking freedom, such as a tenant bound to a manor.
examples: The commissioners then proceeded to consider the various petitions and remonstrances of the unfrees, and to determine the amount to be levied from each.
